codex
I’ve reached the point where the fork state matters more than further theory: there is no live isolated-collateral market to enter, so the only honest code path on this block is “detect and explain infeasibility” before any borrowing logic starts. I’m patching `FlawVerifier.sol` to make that explicit, keep the vulnerable-path implementation intact for forks where an isolated market exists, and expose enough diagnostics to show why this specific fork cannot realize the PoC.
apply patch
